{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-template-excerpt-js","path":"/excerpts/nature_dawn_poem/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Day was destroyed but now reborn,<br>\nCold will gradually become warm,<br>\nDew and wind act to cool skin,<br>\nEyes wake as skies lighten,<br>\nSet to a chorus of birdsong,<br>\nDay appears on the horizon,<br>\nCalm's frail till the clamour's begun,<br>\nThe child of dawn waits to be born,<br>\nSky's filled with pastel blues and reds,<br>\nDarkness is again defeated,<br>\nA shy sun's might barely withheld,<br>\nAn outcome which clockwork foretold,<br>\nMorning light bleeds past the eyelid,<br>\nTentative steps are made while tired,<br>\nThoughts refill a haze filled mind,<br>\nThe dreamland to be left behind.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"January 02, 2020","title":"Dawn","audio":{"publicURL":"/static/cf14ec1c37de8c6510e6c3fc30f01f9b/Christian Lacdael - Nature - 02 Dawn.mp3"},"icon":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/f35dab380c3a6f5f067a4a6db3cc3733/7d509/nature_poem_dawn.jpg","srcSet":"/static/f35dab380c3a6f5f067a4a6db3cc3733/f836f/nature_poem_dawn.jpg 200w,\n/static/f35dab380c3a6f5f067a4a6db3cc3733/2244e/nature_poem_dawn.jpg 400w,\n/static/f35dab380c3a6f5f067a4a6db3cc3733/7d509/nature_poem_dawn.jpg 720w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/excerpts/nature_dawn_poem/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3649515864"]}